      • pluralize

        public static String pluralize(String s)
        Pluralizes a string. The logic is add "s" if the last character is not an "s" with the following exceptions:
        • add "es" if the input string ends with an "s".
        • add "es" if the input string ends with an "x".
        • replace the last character and add "ies" if the input string ends with an "y".
        Parameters:
        s - string to pluralize
        Returns:
        plural string
